{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The review input is scoped to the lines that changed, not the full content of each modified file.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is the handoff between diff extraction and review-input assembly (MOCK-MISS: cross-module invariant). No real OS/network/subprocess is required (REAL-INFRA no). No dependence on model judgment quality (LLM-DEP no). Higher levels rejected: behavior text is about scoping input data, not real API semantics or model output quality.","test_description":"Wire real diff parser + prompt/input builder in-process with fixture diffs containing large unchanged sections; assert emitted review payload includes only changed hunks/lines and excludes unchanged file content.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments are attached to the correct positions in the diff view on the pull request.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Correctness depends on real GitHub diff-position semantics and HTTP API behavior (REAL-INFRA yes, MOCK-HIDE yes). In-process mocks can accept invalid position mapping that GitHub rejects or renders differently. Higher levels rejected: behavior does not require model judgment; it is API/diff mapping correctness.","test_description":"Against a real test PR, post inline comments using computed positions, then read back review comments from GitHub and verify each lands on the intended file/hunk/line in the rendered diff.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.8,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The agent identifies at least one real defect in a pull request that contains a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Pass/fail depends on real model output quality (LLM-DEP yes). Stubbed responses would trivially pass and hide failure to detect the bug (deterministic-assertion trap). Workflow rejected: behavior asks for one detection outcome, not multiple agentic decision stages.","test_description":"Run analysis with the real model on a PR fixture containing a seeded bug; assert at least one returned finding correctly points to that bug location/category with acceptance criteria tolerant to phrasing variance.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Every finding listed in the top-level summary corresponds to a posted inline comment ID from the same run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is a run-local referential-integrity invariant across modules (inline posting result store -> summary builder). It does not inherently require real network or model output (REAL-INFRA no, LLM-DEP no for this behavior). System rejected: behavior text targets ID consistency, not external API semantics.","test_description":"Execute orchestrator in-process with deterministic finding inputs and a fake comment-poster returning unique IDs; assert summary payload contains only IDs emitted in that same run and one-to-one mapping for listed findings.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"No inline finding is dropped from the final summary payload before posting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure appears during multi-module transformation/orchestration (finding set -> posted inline results -> summary payload), not a single pure function in isolation (MOCK-MISS yes). No mandatory real infra or model-quality dependence for this invariant.","test_description":"Run pipeline stages in-process with a fixture set of inline findings (including edge cases like duplicates/ordering); assert final summary payload preserves full expected cardinality/identity before post call.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"The automation sequence (read diff, post inline comments, post summary) succeeds for a real pull request when provided a fixed precomputed finding set.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires a real pull request and real posting sequence, so real HTTP/API and external-system state transitions are part of failure boundary (REAL-INFRA yes). Agentic rejected by behavior text: findings are fixed precomputed, so correctness does not depend on model output.","test_description":"Use a real PR in a test repo, inject fixed findings, run end-to-end sequence, then verify diff read succeeded, inline comments exist on expected files/lines, and top-level summary comment is posted with expected content links/IDs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.86,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"The full live run with model-generated findings (read diff, analyze, post inline comments, post summary) completes correctly for a real pull request without manual intervention.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is a full agent pipeline with real model-generated findings plus downstream posting/orchestration; it combines multiple stages where agentic output governs later actions (MULTI-STEP yes, LLM-DEP yes, REAL-INFRA yes). Lower levels rejected: behavior text explicitly requires full live run and model-generated findings across the whole sequence.","test_description":"Run the production pipeline on a real PR with real model calls enabled; assert completion without human edits/retries, successful inline posting, and consistent summary